      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Missile Drain</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Leon W Zelby letter, responding to May 28 front-page article, questions feasibility of proposed missile defense system (M)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As an electrical engineer who is somewhat familiar with radar, I have always wondered how an antimissile system would be able to differentiate between well-designed decoys and real missiles (front page, May 28).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As an electrical engineer who is somewhat familiar with radar, I have always wondered how an antimissile system would be able to differentiate between well-designed decoys and real missiles (front page, May 28).</p>
        <p>Are we just sending a lot of money down the drain, as we did with Y2K?</p>
        <p>LEON W. ZELBY  Norman, Okla., May 28, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
